{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2015}} {{Infobox person | image = | image_size = | name = August von Finck Jr. | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{bya|1930}} | birth_place = Munich, Germany | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = German | residence = [[Weinfelden Castle]], [[Thurgau]], Switzerland | education = | occupation = Businessman | salary = | networth = [[United States dollar|$]]9.2 billion (September 2018)<ref name=Forbes>{{cite web|title=Forbes profile: August von Finck|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/august-von-finck/|website=Forbes|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref> | spouse = Francine von Finck | parents = [[August von Finck Sr.]] | children = 4 | relatives = | website = }}
'''August von Finck Jr.''' (born 1930) is a Swiss-based German [[billionaire]] businessman.
==Early life== He was born in 1930 in Munich, the son of [[August von Finck Sr.]], and the grandson of [[Wilhelm von Finck]], who started a private bank in 1870 that became Merck Finck & Co.<ref name=Forbes/><ref name="bloomberg.com">{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/billionaires/profiles/august-von-finck/|title=Terms of Service Violation|author=|date=|website=www.bloomberg.com|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref>
==Career== In January 2015, according to [[Forbes]], he had a net worth of $7.7 billion.<ref name=Forbes/>
==Other interests== The German state government of Baden-Württemberg authorized the sale of an incunable about Medieval history to him. The price is around 20 million euros.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.medievalum.com/index.php/se-vende-incunable-medieval/|title=Se vende incunable medieval - Medievalum|author=|date=7 May 2008|website=medievalum.com|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref>
It is likely that Finck is a financial supporter of the German far right party [[Alternative for Germany|AfD]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.heise.de/tp/features/AfD-Die-Masken-fallen-3830717.html|title=AfD: Die Masken fallen|last=Konicz|first=Tomasz|date=14 September 2017|work=TELEPOLIS|access-date=19 September 2017|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=}}</ref>
==Personal life== He is married to Francine.<ref name="bloomberg.com"/> They have four children and live in [[Weinfelden Castle]] in [[Thurgau]] canton, Switzerland.<ref name=Forbes/><ref name="bloomberg.com"/> His eldest son is [[August François von Finck]].
