'''Gordon "Butch" Stewart''' [[Order of Jamaica|OJ]], [[Commander of the Order of Distinction|CD]] (born 6 July 1941) is a Jamaican [[hotelier]] and businessman. He is the founder and chairman of [[Sandals Resorts]] and [[Beaches Resorts]].

==Career==
Stewart began working at the age of 17 as a salesman and eventually rose to become the sales manager of Dutch-owned Curaçao Trading Company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.inc.com/magazine/20080401/how-i-did-it-butch-stewart-sandals-resorts.html|title=How I Did It: Butch Stewart of Sandals Resorts|author=|date=1 April 2008|website=inc.com|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref> After saving up some money, Stewart later left in 1968 to find his own business, Appliance Traders, Ltd. which specialized at first in importing and selling air conditioning units, water coolers and stoves but has grown to sell almost everything.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.grenadianconnection.com/blkheroes/blackHistory.asp?headline=3|title=News|author=|date=|website=www.grenadianconnection.com|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref> The company also founded the Jamaica Observer newspaper.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thecaribbeancurrent.com/the-story-of-gordon-butch-stewart-and-sandals-resorts|title=The Story of Gordon Butch Stewart and Sandals Resorts|author=|date=16 March 2013|website=thecaribbeancurrent.com|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref>

In 1981 Stewart purchased two hotels and began to turn the venture into a profit. A number of years later he purchased [[Sandals Resorts]] Royal Caribbean which catered to an adult-only clientele. [[Beaches Resorts|Beaches]] was developed for families, while the company expanded around the Caribbean.<ref name="Story Of Gordon">[http://thecaribbeancurrent.com/the-story-of-gordon-butch-stewart-and-sandals-resorts/ "Story of Gorden Steward"] Johnny Ringo, 'The Story of Gordon 'Butch' Stewart' and Sandals Resorts' ''Caribbean Current'', 16 March 2013</ref>

Most recently, Stewart founded Sandals Corporate University, aimed at providing professional development for employees through reputable education and training programs. With access to more than 230 courses and external partnerships with 13 top-ranking local and international universities, every staff member has the opportunity to apply, broaden their knowledge and advance their career.{{citation needed|date=January 2017}}

===Personal life===
His son, [[Adam Stewart (business executive)|Adam Stewart]] is CEO and Deputy Chairman of Sandals Resorts International and president of the Sandals Foundation. His daughter Jamie Stewart-McConnell was formerly a brand manager at Royal Plantation,<ref>[http://jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20120202/cook/cook2.html "Orijin article"] Barbara Ellington, 'Stewart-McConnell Gives Birth To Orijin', ''Jamaica Gleaner'', 2 February 2012</ref> while his eldest son Brian Jardim sits on the Board of the Jamaica Observer and is the owner of Rainforest, a seafood import company.<ref>[http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/news/Brian-Jardim-named-to-Observer-board_11706056 "Brian Jardim"] Staffwriter, 'Brian Jardim named to Observer board' Jamaica Observer, 15 June 2012</ref> One of his sons, Jonathan, was killed in a car crash in 1990.<ref name="Sandals family interview">[http://www.travelweekly.co.uk/articles/2009/01/15/29977/interview-the-stewarts-on-sandals-business-and-family.html "Sandals interview"] Judith Baker, 'Interview: The Stewarts on Sandals, business and family values', ''Travel Weekly'', 15 January 2009</ref>

==Honours and awards==
Stewart’s successes in business and in life have earned him more than fifty{{citation needed|date=January 2017}} local, regional and international accolades and awards including Jamaica’s highest national distinctions: The Order of Jamaica, and Commander of the Order of Distinction. He is the 2001 recipient of the honorary Doctor of Laws (LLD) from the University of the West Indies and also the 2009 recipient from the University of Technology.  In 1992, Stewart was presented with the Martin Luther King Jr. Humanitarian Award in recognition of his tireless efforts to advance humanity.  Emst & Young voted him Master Entrepreneur of the decade of the 90s.  Stewart is a Paul Harris Fellow, Rotary International's highest award. At the 2000 World Travel Awards, he was voted “Travel Man of the Millennium” for his work in promoting Caribbean tourism.  In 2011, The Caribbean American Foundation presented Stewart with the Golden Eagle Humanitarian Award in recognition of his philanthropic contributions to education and entrepreneurship in the Caribbean. In 2014 Stewart was honored with the Most Innovative All-Inclusive Resort Executive by the Travalliance Travvy Awards, Hotelier of the Year at the Cacique Award held by the Bahamas Ministry of Tourism and the Invest Caribbean Now Leadership Award presented at its global summit.{{fact|date=September 2018}}

Stewart was a recipient of ''Caribbean World'' Magazine's Lifetime Achievement Award for his work in Jamaica,<ref name="bsun">{{Cite web|url=http://www.bermudasun.bm/main.asp?SectionID=72&SubSectionID=205&ArticleID=36464&TM=76902.07|title=Lifetime Achievement Award for Jefferis|accessdate=2008-02-10|date=1 February 2008|work=Bermuda Sun}}</ref> and has been called one of Jamaica's most-admired businessmen, by Kamal King President of Cambridge College and Community Services Jamaica in an address to graduating students.<ref name="admire">{{Cite web|url=http://www.jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20060322/business/business1.html |title=Jamaica's Most Admired Business Leaders |accessdate=2008-02-10 |date=22 March 2006 |work=Jamaica Gleaner |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080413193306/http://www.jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20060322/business/business1.html |archivedate=13 April 2008 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref name="inc">{{Cite web|url=https://www.inc.com/magazine/20080401/how-i-did-it-butch-stewart-sandals-resorts.html|title=How I Did It: Butch Stewart of Sandals Resorts|accessdate=2018-06-06|date=1 April 2008|work=inc.com}}</ref>

He has earned Lifetime Achievement Awards from The American Academy of Hospitality Sciences, Travel Weekly and Globe Travel Awards and was awarded an honorary Doctorate of Business Administration in hospitality authority, Johnson & Wales University.{{fact|date=September 2018}}

