'''Raymond Pitcairn''' (1885 – July 12, 1966), son of [[PPG Industries]] founder [[John Pitcairn, Jr.|John Pitcairn]], was a lawyer, a businessman, a collector of ancient and medieval art, and an amateur architect. He supervised the building of the [[Bryn Athyn Cathedral]] and his own castle-mansion of [[Glencairn Museum|Glencairn]].<ref name="dynasty">{{Citation | last = Jaffe | first = Dennis T. | author-link =  | last2 = Jungé | first2 = Dirk | author2-link =  | last3 = Paul | first3 = Joseph | title = Reinventing a family dynasty | journal = : Family Business Magazine | volume =  | issue = Winter | pages =  | date =  | year = 2004 | url = http://www.dennisjaffe.com/articles/PitcairnFamily.pdf | doi =  | id =  | postscript = <!--none--> | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090106042717/http://www.dennisjaffe.com/articles/PitcairnFamily.pdf | archivedate = 2009-01-06 | df =  }}
</ref>

Pitcairn was also quite politically active. A Republican, he served as one of the delegates to Pennsylvania's convention to ratify the [[Twenty-first Amendment to the United States Constitution|Twenty-first Amendment]] in 1933, and was one of Pennsylvania's delegates to the [[1956 Republican National Convention]].
<ref name="polticalgraveyard">{{cite web | last = Kestenbaum | first = Lawrence | authorlink = | coauthors = | title = The Political Graveyard | work = | publisher = | date = | url = http://politicalgraveyard.com/bio/pinkerton-pittoni.html | doi = | accessdate = 2008-11-14}}</ref> He was also the national chairman and a major financial supporter of the [[Sentinels of the Republic]], a conservative political group of the 1920s and 1930s which opposed the expansion of federal regulation and the [[New Deal]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Balch|first=Katharin|title=Sentinels of the Republic|url=http://www.lib.utulsa.edu/digital/robertson/Series_II/pdf/AR2_20_01_1874.pdf|accessdate=13 February 2013}}</ref>

Pitcairn died on July 12, 1966, and was buried at Bryn Athyn Cemetery, in [[Bryn Athyn, Pennsylvania]].<ref name="polticalgraveyard" />

